            "content": [
              {
                "type": "output_text",
                "text": "Here are the latest service updates for the London Underground between December 5-7, 2025:\n\n1. **Northern Line**: No service between Archway and High Barnet/Mill Hill East after 5:30 AM on Saturday and Sunday. Additionally, no service between Charing Cross and Golders Green/High Barnet from 1:45 AM to 5:30 AM [Timeout](https://www.timeout.com/london/news/london-travel-disruption-this-weekend-full-list-of-tube-and-train-closures-for-december-5-7-2025-120425).\n\n2. **Piccadilly Line**: Closed between Acton Town and Uxbridge on Saturday and Sunday [Timeout](https://www.timeout.com/london/news/london-travel-disruption-this-weekend-full-list-of-tube-and-train-closures-for-december-5-7-2025-120425).\n\n3. **Metropolitan Line**: No service between Harrow-on-the-Hill and Uxbridge on Saturday and Sunday [Traffic Delays](https://www.trafficdelays.co.uk/london-trains/).\n\n4. **Elizabeth Line**: Sunday morning closure between Paddington and Ealing Broadway [HotMinute](https://hotminute.co.uk/2025/12/05/london-tube-and-train-disruptions-this-weekend-5-7-december/).\n\n5. **DLR**: No service between Shadwell and Tower Gateway on Sunday [Lawyer Monthly](https://www.lawyer-monthly.com/2025/12/london-travel-disruption-weekend-tube-rail-closures/).\n\nPlease check for updates before traveling, as schedules can change ([TfL](https://tfl.gov.uk/status-updates/planned-track-closures)).",
